jcr:content.jcr:title: Jeff Browning

text.text: Jeff Browning (aka Bronco Billy) is an online endurance coach and veteran ultrarunner of more than two decades. At 49, he continues to rip it up in some of the worldâ€™s most rugged ultramarathons. With more than 30 career ultra-wins, he holds multiple course records, including The Double record for the fastest combined times of Western States 100 and Hardrock 100 (a mere 19 days apart). When not on the trail, Jeff can be found chatting with the local rancher at the summer farmerâ€™s market or conversing with neighborhood baristas about the benefits of an ancestral diet.

image.alt: Black and white icon of a trophy

text_copy.text:
Accomplishments:

  • Being married for 24 years!  

  • Over 30 career ultra-wins (21 in 100-milers).  

  • Only one DNF (badly rolled ankle) in 21 years of running ultras (over 150 finishes).

image.alt: Black and white icon of a stopwatch

text_copy.text:
How fast do you think you could run a backwards mile?
 
Slow enough not to fall and bust my noggin.

image.alt: Black and white icon of a heart

text.text:
What is one of your most memorable non-competition runs?

Running across Patagonia National Park in Chile.

image.alt: Black and white icon of a flag
